{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":1,"author":{"id":"04135dc995e2fdcd322aaf4268dbf04630a3cc7c"},"timestamp":1481211669,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUxOTQzNjgyNzA=","github-url":"https://github.com/perl11/cperl/issues/232","origin":"github"},"title":"Fix mixed-script unicode names in tests","message":"The various unicode tests are filled with random chunk of unicode characters, which do not make up proper names. They need to readable, good identifiers, and esp. using a single script, not a mix of e.g. Greek and Cyrillic, where most characters are different but confusable.\n\ne.g. `uni/stash.t` uses those scripts: \n\n             Katakana Vai Saurashtra Canadian_Aboriginal Runic Coptic\n             Yi Hangul Oriya Ogham Tai_Viet Cyrillic Bopomofo Kannada\n             Tamil Hiragana Glagolitic\n\nnobody is able to read all those languages.\n\nto be able to use unicode one should not rely on exotic unreadable names. there are enough unicode names in the latin script \u003e 128.\nand esp. do not mix scripts from different languages.\n\nso far fixed with ed3c5a1df01fa197acba1392b0394ccf3b0ca100 and aebe81703814ca50e7d6fdb97554a73db5d91f3f are:\nt/uni/package.t, t/uni/select.t and t/mro/basic_03_c3_utf8.t (Hangul only)\n\ntodo:\n```\nt/uni/attrs.t\nt/uni/goto.t\nt/uni/gv.t\nt/uni/method.t\nt/uni/parser.t\nt/uni/readline.t\nt/uni/stash.t\n\nt/mro/basic_01_c3_utf8.t\nt/mro/basic_01_dfs_utf8.t\nt/mro/basic_02_c3_utf8.t\nt/mro/basic_02_dfs_utf8.t\nt/mro/basic_03_c3_utf8.t\nt/mro/basic_03_dfs_utf8.t\nt/mro/basic_04_c3_utf8.t\nt/mro/basic_04_dfs_utf8.t\nt/mro/basic_05_c3_utf8.t\nt/mro/basic_05_dfs_utf8.t\nt/mro/basic_utf8.t\nt/mro/complex_c3_utf8.t\nt/mro/complex_dfs_utf8.t\nt/mro/dbic_c3_utf8.t\nt/mro/dbic_dfs_utf8.t\nt/mro/isa_aliases_utf8.t\nt/mro/isa_c3_utf8.t\nt/mro/isa_dfs_utf8.t\nt/mro/isarev_utf8.t\nt/mro/method_caching_utf8.t\nt/mro/next_NEXT_utf8.t\nt/mro/next_edgecases_utf8.t\nt/mro/next_goto_utf8.t\nt/mro/next_inanon_utf8.t\nt/mro/next_ineval_utf8.t\nt/mro/next_method_utf8.t\nt/mro/next_skip_utf8.t\nt/mro/overload_c3_utf8.t\nt/mro/package_aliases_utf8.t\nt/mro/pkg_gen_utf8.t\nt/mro/recursion_c3_utf8.t\nt/mro/recursion_dfs_utf8.t\nt/mro/vulcan_c3_utf8.t\nt/mro/vulcan_dfs_utf8.t\n```\n\nmaybe write a simple script, parsing all these tests for unicode words, and replacing them with better words.","files":null}]}